    <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
        <body>
            <div xml:id="KT384-kilavi">
                <p type="edition">“niṉ parattaiyaṟku nī uṟṟa cūḷuṟavu naṉṟāy iruntatu” eṉṟu
                    nakaiyāṭit tōḻi vāyiṉ maṟuttatu. </p>


                <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">The door refused by the confidante in jest,
                    saying “it is excellent to have the oath, which you have made to your other
                    women.” </p>
            </div>

            <div xml:id="KT384">
                <lg type="edition">
                    <l> uḻuntuṭaik kaḻutiṟ karumpuṭaip paṇaittō</l>
                    <l> ṇeṭumpal kūntaṟ kuṟuntoṭi makaḷir</l>
                    <l> nalaṉuṇṭu tuṟatti yāyiṉ</l>
                    <l> mikanaṉ ṟamma makiḻnaniṉ cūḷē.</l>


                </lg>

                <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                    <l rend="indent"> If you give [her] up, having eaten [her] innocence,</l>
                    <l rend="indent2"> [for] women with tight bracelets, long many tresses</l>
                    <l rend="indent8"> [and] bamboo shoulders</l>
                    <l rend="indent2"> with sugarcane [drawing ], on the platform for [guarding]</l>
                    <l rend="indent8"> the black gram [field,</l>
                    <l> very good, alas, delightful man, [is] your oath.</l>

                    <lg type="alternate" sameAs="2+3b" resp="#TVG">
                        <l>If you give up, having eaten [their] innocence,</l>
                        <l>the women with tight bracelets ...</l>
                    </lg>
                </lg>
            </div>
        </body>
